From: Andy Lutomirski <luto@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 3 Oct 2018 16:23:49 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] x86/vdso: Fix vDSO syscall fallback asm constraint regression
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.18.14
Git-commit: 02e425668f5c9deb42787d10001a3b605993ad15

commit 02e425668f5c9deb42787d10001a3b605993ad15 upstream.

When I added the missing memory outputs, I failed to update the
index of the first argument (ebx) on 32-bit builds, which broke the
fallbacks.  Somehow I must have screwed up my testing or gotten
lucky.

Add another test to cover gettimeofday() as well.

